  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: only on big iOS screens (iphone 7 plus): When emoji keyboard is opened then no input field is shown, so user can't see what emoji are typed and can't see send button.\r\n![16968](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6584810/36793545-f4ce9044-1c9d-11e8-81d8-ae187e926058.jpg)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nInput field and send button are shown, so user can see its content when typing emoji and can send them\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nWhen emoji keyboard is opened then no input field is shown, so user can't see what emoji are typed and can't see send button.\r\n### Reproduction\r\nvideo (00:17) https://app.testfairy.com/projects/4803590-status/builds/7798752/sessions/18/?accessToken=iSJnsGm5/SNdV7BwOnDnljFZgTk\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Open 1:1 chat\r\n- tap on emoji device keyboard and tap on emoji. Check if input field is shown and you can send typed emojis\r\n- switch to text keyboard, type \"hello\" and switch to emoji keyboard. Tap on any emoji. Check if input field is shown and you can send typed emojis\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: nightly build Feb 28\r\n* Operating System: iPhone 7 plus, iOS 11.0.3.\r\n",
